cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.PF, cs.DC, cs.ET

Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a framework for autonomous learning of the configuration in DC MicroGrids, which involves control and estimation of the system dynamics. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The framework employs Maximum Likelihood Estimation procedure for system identification, which is a common machine learning technique. 
- cs.PF (Performance): The paper discusses the practical potential of the proposed framework, which relates to the performance of the system. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The framework is implemented within the decentralized primary droop control loop, which involves distributed computing. 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): The paper deals with the application of advanced technologies (such as power electronic converters) in DC MicroGrids, which is an emerging area of research.
